msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc3:pts-cs0.5"
msgid "3. Pesuññasikkhāpada"
msgstr "The training rule on malicious talebearing"

#. </h1></div><h2>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc3:pts-cs1.0a"
msgid ""
msgstr "Origin story"

#. </h2><p><a class="sc" id="1"></a><a class="pts-vp-pli" id="pts-vp-pli4.12"></a><a class="pts-cs" id="bu-pc.3.1"></a><a class="pts-vp-en" id="BD.2.186"></a><a class="wt-pa" id="wt-pa111"></a> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc3:pts-cs1.1"
msgid ""
"Tena samayena buddho bhagavā sāvatthiyaṃ viharati jetavane anāthapiṇḍikassa "
"ārāme."
msgstr ""
"At one time the Buddha was staying at Sāvatthī in the Jeta Grove, "
"Anāthapiṇḍika’s Monastery."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc3:pts-cs1.2"
msgid ""
"Tena kho pana samayena chabbaggiyā bhikkhū bhikkhūnaṃ bhaṇḍanajātānaṃ "
"kalahajātānaṃ vivādāpannānaṃ pesuññaṃ upasaṃharanti;"
msgstr ""
"At that time the monks from the group of six were engaged in malicious "
"talebearing between monks who were arguing."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc3:pts-cs1.3"
msgid ""
"imassa sutvā amussa akkhāyanti, imassa bhedāya; amussa sutvā imassa "
"akkhāyanti, amussa bhedāya."
msgstr ""
"After hearing something on one side they reported it to the other side, and "
"vice versa, in order to create division between them."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc3:pts-cs1.4"
msgid ""
"Tena anuppannāni ceva bhaṇḍanāni uppajjanti, uppannāni ca bhaṇḍanāni "
"bhiyyobhāvāya vepullāya saṃvattanti."
msgstr ""
"In this way new quarrels were created and existing quarrels became worse."

#. </p><p>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc3:pts-cs1.5"
msgid "Ye te bhikkhū appicchā … pe …"
msgstr "The monks of few desires …"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc3:pts-cs1.6"
msgid "te ujjhāyanti khiyyanti vipācenti—"
msgstr "complained and criticized them,"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc3:pts-cs1.7"
msgid ""
"“kathañhi nāma chabbaggiyā bhikkhū bhikkhūnaṃ bhaṇḍanajātānaṃ kalahajātānaṃ "
"vivādāpannānaṃ pesuññaṃ upasaṃharissanti, imassa sutvā amussa akkhāyissanti, "
"imassa bhedāya;"
msgstr ""
"“How can the monks from the group of six engage in malicious talebearing "
"between monks who are arguing?"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc3:pts-cs1.8"
msgid "amussa sutvā imassa akkhāyissanti, amussa bhedāya."
msgstr ""
"How can they report to one side what they have heard on the other side, and "
"vice versa, in order to create division,"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc3:pts-cs1.9"
msgid ""
"Tena anuppannāni ceva bhaṇḍanāni uppajjanti, uppannāni ca bhaṇḍanāni "
"bhiyyobhāvāya vepullāya saṃvattantī”ti."
msgstr "and in this way create new quarrels and make existing quarrels worse?”"

#. </p><p><a class="sc" id="2"></a><a class="wt-pa" id="wt-pa112"></a> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc3:pts-cs1.10"
msgid ""
"Atha kho te bhikkhū chabbaggiye bhikkhū anekapariyāyena vigarahitvā "
"bhagavato etamatthaṃ ārocesuṃ … pe …"
msgstr "After criticizing those monks in many ways, they told the Master. …"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc3:pts-cs1.11"
msgid ""
"“saccaṃ kira tumhe, bhikkhave, bhikkhūnaṃ bhaṇḍanajātānaṃ kalahajātānaṃ "
"vivādāpannānaṃ pesuññaṃ upasaṃharatha, imassa sutvā amussa akkhāyatha, "
"imassa bhedāya, amussa sutvā imassa akkhāyatha, amussa bhedāya?"
msgstr "“Is it true, monks, that you do this?”"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc3:pts-cs1.12"
msgid ""
"Tena anuppannāni ceva bhaṇḍanāni uppajjanti, uppannāni ca bhaṇḍanāni "
"bhiyyobhāvāya vepullāya saṃvattantī”ti?"
msgstr ""

#. </p><p>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc3:pts-cs1.13"
msgid "“Saccaṃ, bhagavā”ti."
msgstr "“It’s true, Master.”"

#. </p><p>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc3:pts-cs1.14"
msgid "Vigarahi buddho bhagavā … pe …"
msgstr "The Buddha rebuked them,"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc3:pts-cs1.15"
msgid ""
"kathañhi nāma tumhe, moghapurisā, bhikkhūnaṃ bhaṇḍanajātānaṃ kalahajātānaṃ "
"vivādāpannānaṃ pesuññaṃ upasaṃharissatha."
msgstr ""
"“… Foolish men, how can you engage in malicious talebearing between monks "
"who are arguing?"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc3:pts-cs1.16"
msgid ""
"Imassa sutvā amussa akkhāyissatha, imassa bhedāya. Amussa sutvā imassa "
"akkhāyissatha, amussa bhedāya."
msgstr ""
"How can you report to one side what you have heard on the other side, and "
"vice versa, in order to create division,"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc3:pts-cs1.17"
msgid ""
"Tena anuppannāni ceva bhaṇḍanāni uppajjanti, uppannāni ca bhaṇḍanāni "
"bhiyyobhāvāya vepullāya saṃvattanti."
msgstr "and in this way create new quarrels and make existing quarrels worse?"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc3:pts-cs1.18"
msgid "Netaṃ, moghapurisā, appasannānaṃ vā pasādāya."
msgstr "This will not give rise to confidence in those without it"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc3:pts-cs1.19"
msgid "Pasannānaṃ vā bhiyyobhāvāya … pe …"
msgstr "or increase the confidence of those who have it …"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc3:pts-cs1.20"
msgid "evañca pana, bhikkhave, imaṃ sikkhāpadaṃ uddiseyyātha—"
msgstr "And, monks, this training rule should be recited thus:"

#. </p><h2>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc3:pts-cs1.20a"
msgid ""
msgstr "Final ruling"

#. </h2><p><a class="sc" id="3"></a><a class="wt-pa" id="wt-pa113"></a>
#. <span class="rule">
#. This is translated somewhat freely in accordance with the explanation below and in the commentary. According to <ref>MS.2.144</ref> (see below) the offense is only incurred when a monk brings the words of another monk to the attention of yet another monk, and thus the translation “between monks.” <ref>Sp.4.740.20</ref> supports the plural rendering “monks”: “malicious talebearing of monks,” <i lang="pli">bhikkhūnaṃ pesuññe</i>.
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc3:pts-cs1.21"
msgid "“Bhikkhupesuññe pācittiyan”ti."
msgstr ""
"‘If a monk engages in malicious talebearing between monks, he commits an "
"offense entailing confession.’”"

#. </span> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc3:pts-cs1.22"
msgid "(<em>3</em>:<strong>52</strong>)"
msgstr ""

#. </p><h2>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc3:pts-cs2.1.0a"
msgid ""
msgstr "Definitions"

#. </h2><p><a class="sc" id="4"></a><a class="pts-cs-empty" id="bu-pc.3.2"></a><a class="pts-cs" id="bu-pc.3.2.1"></a><a class="pts-vp-en" id="BD.2.187"></a><a class="wt-pa" id="wt-pa114"></a>
#. <span class="term"> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc3:pts-cs2.1.1"
msgid "Pesuññaṃ nāma"
msgstr "Malicious talebearing:"

#. </span><span class="gloss"> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc3:pts-cs2.1.2"
msgid "dvīhākārehi pesuññaṃ hoti—"
msgstr "there is malicious talebearing in two ways:"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc3:pts-cs2.1.3"
msgid "piyakamyassa vā bhedādhippāyassa vā."
msgstr "for one wanting to endear himself or for one aiming at division."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc3:pts-cs2.1.4"
msgid "Dasahākārehi pesuññaṃ upasaṃharati—"
msgstr "One engages in malicious talebearing in ten ways:"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc3:pts-cs2.1.5"
msgid ""
"jātitopi, nāmatopi, gottatopi, kammatopi, sippatopi, ābādhatopi, liṅgatopi, "
"kilesatopi, āpattitopi, akkosatopi."
msgstr ""
"about caste, about name, about family, about work, about craft, about "
"illnesses, about physical traits, about defilements, about offenses, and by "
"insulting."

#. </span></p><h2>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc3:pts-cs2.1.5a"
msgid ""
msgstr "Permutations"

#. </h2><h3>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc3:pts-cs2.1.5b"
msgid ""
msgstr "Permutations part 1"

#. </h3><h4>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc3:pts-cs2.1.5c"
msgid ""
msgstr "Definitions"

#. </h4><p><a class="sc" id="5"></a><a class="wt-pa" id="wt-pa115"></a>
#. <span class="term"> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc3:pts-cs2.1.6"
msgid "Jāti nāma"
msgstr "Caste:"

#. </span><span class="gloss"> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc3:pts-cs2.1.7"
msgid "dve jātiyo—"
msgstr "there are two kinds of castes:"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc3:pts-cs2.1.8"
msgid "hīnā ca jāti ukkaṭṭhā ca jāti."
msgstr "low castes and high castes."

#. <span class="term"> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc3:pts-cs2.1.9"
msgid "Hīnā nāma"
msgstr "Low castes:"

#. </span><span class="gloss"> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc3:pts-cs2.1.10"
msgid "jāti—caṇḍālajāti venajāti nesādajāti rathakārajāti pukkusajāti."
msgstr "outcasts, bamboo workers, hunters, chariot-makers, waste-removers—"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc3:pts-cs2.1.11"
msgid "Esā hīnā nāma jāti."
msgstr "these are called “low castes.”"

#. </span><span class="term"> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc3:pts-cs2.1.12"
msgid "Ukkaṭṭhā nāma"
msgstr "High castes:"

#. </span><span class="gloss"> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc3:pts-cs2.1.13"
msgid "jāti—khattiyajāti brāhmaṇajāti."
msgstr "aristocrats and brahmins—"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc3:pts-cs2.1.14"
msgid "Esā ukkaṭṭhā nāma jāti … pe …."
msgstr ""
"these are called “high castes.” … <span class=\"pe\">To be expanded as in <a "
"class=\"cr\" href=\"./pli-tv-bu-vb-pc2#9\">Pācittiya 2, paragraphs "
"9–16</a>.</span> …"

#. </span></span></p><p><a class="sc" id="6"></a><a class="pts-vp-pli" id="pts-vp-pli4.13"></a><a class="wt-pa" id="wt-pa116"></a>
#. <span class="term"> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc3:pts-cs2.1.15"
msgid "Akkoso nāma"
msgstr "Insults:"

#. </span><span class="gloss"> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc3:pts-cs2.1.16"
msgid "dve akkosā—"
msgstr "there are two kinds of insults:"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc3:pts-cs2.1.17"
msgid "hīno ca akkoso ukkaṭṭho ca akkoso."
msgstr "low insults and high insults."

#. <span class="term"> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc3:pts-cs2.1.18"
msgid "Hīno nāma"
msgstr "Low insults:"

#. </span><span class="gloss"> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc3:pts-cs2.1.19"
msgid ""
"akkoso—“oṭṭhosi, meṇḍosi, goṇosi, gadrabhosi, tiracchānagatosi, nerayikosi; "
"natthi tuyhaṃ sugati; duggatiyeva tuyhaṃ pāṭikaṅkhā”ti, yakārena vā "
"bhakārena vā kāṭakoṭacikāya vā."
msgstr ""
"“you’re a camel/you’re a ram/you’re an ox/you’re a donkey/you’re an "
"animal/you’re bound for hell/you’re not going to a good destination/you can "
"only expect a bad destination,” or adding the disparaging endings <i lang=\""
"pli\">ya</i> or <i lang=\"pli\">bha</i> to someone’s name, or calling "
"someone words for the male and female genitals—"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc3:pts-cs2.1.20"
msgid "Eso hīno nāma akkoso."
msgstr "these are called “low insults.”"

#. </span><span class="term"> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc3:pts-cs2.1.21"
msgid "Ukkaṭṭho nāma"
msgstr "High insults:"

#. </span><span class="gloss"> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc3:pts-cs2.1.22"
msgid ""
"akkoso—“paṇḍitosi, byattosi, medhāvīsi, bahussutosi, dhammakathikosi; natthi "
"tuyhaṃ duggati; sugatiyeva tuyhaṃ pāṭikaṅkhā”ti."
msgstr ""
"“you’re wise/you’re competent/you’re intelligent/you’re learned/you’re an "
"expounder of the Teaching/you’re not going to a bad destination/you can only "
"expect a good destination”—"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc3:pts-cs2.1.23"
msgid "Eso ukkaṭṭho nāma akkoso."
msgstr "these are called “high insults.”"

#. </span></span>
#. </p><h4>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc3:pts-cs2.2.0a"
msgid ""
msgstr "Exposition"

#. </h4><h5>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc3:pts-cs2.2.0b"
msgid ""
msgstr "Direct abuse"

#. </h5><p><a class="sc" id="7"></a><a class="pts-cs" id="bu-pc.3.2.2"></a><a class="wt-pa" id="wt-pa117"></a> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc3:pts-cs2.2.1"
msgid "Upasampanno upasampannassa sutvā upasampannassa pesuññaṃ upasaṃharati—"
msgstr ""
"If one who is fully ordained, after hearing it from another who is fully "
"ordained, engages in malicious talebearing by saying to yet another who is "
"fully ordained,"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc3:pts-cs2.2.2"
msgid "“itthannāmo taṃ ‘caṇḍālo veno nesādo rathakāro pukkuso’ti bhaṇatī”ti."
msgstr ""
"“So-and-so says this about you, ‘He’s an outcast/he’s a bamboo worker/he’s a "
"hunter/he’s a chariot-maker/he’s a waste-remover,’”"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc3:pts-cs2.2.3"
msgid "Āpatti vācāya, vācāya pācittiyassa."
msgstr "then for every statement, he commits an offense entailing confession."

#. </p><p><a class="sc" id="8"></a><a class="wt-pa" id="wt-pa118"></a> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc3:pts-cs2.2.4"
msgid "Upasampanno upasampannassa sutvā upasampannassa pesuññaṃ upasaṃharati—"
msgstr ""
"If one who is fully ordained, after hearing it from another who is fully "
"ordained, engages in malicious talebearing by saying to yet another who is "
"fully ordained,"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc3:pts-cs2.2.5"
msgid "“itthannāmo taṃ ‘khattiyo brāhmaṇo’ti bhaṇatī”ti."
msgstr "“So-and-so says this about you, ‘He’s an aristocrat/he’s a brahmin,’”"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc3:pts-cs2.2.6"
msgid "Āpatti vācāya, vācāya pācittiyassa."
msgstr "then for every statement, he commits an offense entailing confession."

#. </p><hr><p><a class="sc" id="9"></a><a class="wt-pa" id="wt-pa119"></a> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc3:pts-cs2.2.7"
msgid "Upasampanno upasampannassa sutvā upasampannassa pesuññaṃ upasaṃharati—"
msgstr ""
"If one who is fully ordained, after hearing it from another who is fully "
"ordained, engages in malicious talebearing by saying to yet another who is "
"fully ordained,"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc3:pts-cs2.2.8"
msgid ""
"“itthannāmo taṃ ‘avakaṇṇako javakaṇṇako dhaniṭṭhako saviṭṭhako kulavaḍḍhako’"
"ti bhaṇatī”ti."
msgstr ""
"“So-and-so says this about you, ‘He’s an Avakaṇṇaka/he’s a Javakaṇṇaka/he’s "
"a Dhaniṭṭhaka/he’s a Saviṭṭhaka/he’s a Kulavaḍḍhaka,’”"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc3:pts-cs2.2.9"
msgid "Āpatti vācāya, vācāya pācittiyassa."
msgstr "then for every statement, he commits an offense entailing confession."

#. </p><p><a class="sc" id="10"></a><a class="wt-pa" id="wt-pa120"></a> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc3:pts-cs2.2.10"
msgid "Upasampanno upasampannassa sutvā upasampannassa pesuññaṃ upasaṃharati—"
msgstr ""
"If one who is fully ordained, after hearing it from another who is fully "
"ordained, engages in malicious talebearing by saying to yet another who is "
"fully ordained,"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc3:pts-cs2.2.11"
msgid ""
"“itthannāmo taṃ ‘buddharakkhito dhammarakkhito saṃgharakkhito’ti bhaṇatī”ti."
msgstr ""
"“So-and-so says this about you, ‘He’s a Buddharakkhita/he’s a "
"Dhammarakkhita/he’s a Sangharakkhita,’”"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc3:pts-cs2.2.12"
msgid "Āpatti vācāya, vācāya pācittiyassa."
msgstr "then for every statement, he commits an offense entailing confession."

#. </p><hr><p><a class="sc" id="11"></a><a class="wt-pa" id="wt-pa121"></a> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc3:pts-cs2.2.13"
msgid "Upasampanno upasampannassa sutvā upasampannassa pesuññaṃ upasaṃharati—"
msgstr ""
"If one who is fully ordained, after hearing it from another who is fully "
"ordained, engages in malicious talebearing by saying to yet another who is "
"fully ordained,"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc3:pts-cs2.2.14"
msgid "“itthannāmo taṃ ‘kosiyo bhāradvājo’ti bhaṇatī”ti."
msgstr "“So-and-so says this about you, ‘He’s a Kosiya/he’s a Bhāradvāja,’”"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc3:pts-cs2.2.15"
msgid "Āpatti vācāya, vācāya pācittiyassa."
msgstr "then for every statement, he commits an offense entailing confession."

#. </p><p><a class="sc" id="12"></a><a class="wt-pa" id="wt-pa122"></a> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc3:pts-cs2.2.16"
msgid "Upasampanno upasampannassa sutvā upasampannassa pesuññaṃ upasaṃharati—"
msgstr ""
"If one who is fully ordained, after hearing it from another who is fully "
"ordained, engages in malicious talebearing by saying to yet another who is "
"fully ordained,"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc3:pts-cs2.2.17"
msgid "“itthannāmo taṃ ‘gotamo moggallāno kaccāno vāsiṭṭho’ti bhaṇatī”ti."
msgstr ""
"“So-and-so says this about you, ‘He’s a Gotama/he’s a Moggallāna/he’s a "
"Kaccāna/he’s a Vāsiṭṭha,’”"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc3:pts-cs2.2.18"
msgid "Āpatti vācāya, vācāya pācittiyassa."
msgstr "then for every statement, he commits an offense entailing confession."

#. </p><hr><p><a class="sc" id="13"></a><a class="wt-pa" id="wt-pa123"></a> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc3:pts-cs2.2.19"
msgid "Upasampanno upasampannassa sutvā upasampannassa pesuññaṃ upasaṃharati—"
msgstr ""
"If one who is fully ordained, after hearing it from another who is fully "
"ordained, engages in malicious talebearing by saying to yet another who is "
"fully ordained,"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc3:pts-cs2.2.20"
msgid "“itthannāmo taṃ ‘koṭṭhako pupphachaḍḍako’ti bhaṇatī”ti."
msgstr ""
"“So-and-so says this about you, ‘He’s a carpenter/he’s a waste-remover,’”"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc3:pts-cs2.2.21"
msgid "Āpatti vācāya, vācāya pācittiyassa."
msgstr "then for every statement, he commits an offense entailing confession."

